Native unit tests for the 80 mm pipe-valve controller live in
`test/test_controller`.

Run them with:

```powershell
platformio test -e native
```

The tests avoid real MCU hardware by using fake implementations of
`StepperPort`, `UartPort`, `DelayPort`, and `EventSink`.
Current coverage includes controller timing, homing, StallGuard fallback,
persistent settings, serial commands, Modbus RTU edge cases and TMC2209 UART.
Fault recovery is covered with the `REFRESH` command and Modbus command `5`,
so tests verify that a failed machine can rehome without an MCU reset.
The current native suite contains 105 test cases, including motor-disable on
fault, blocked HOME-after-fault behavior, soft-endstop write rejection while
faulted, Modbus broadcast safety, multi-register atomicity, dual-sector
settings journaling, debounced boot sanity, no-progress supervision,
read-only diagnostic registers `17..22`, degree target/current/limit registers
`23..26`, StallGuard threshold register `27`, homing/motor configuration,
Auto-Home interval register `36`, boot-reason readout, non-moving `SELFTEST?`
service diagnostics, explicit TMC2209 communication-health reporting and
UART-polled driver fault reporting without a DIAG pin.
